- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely because the paper deals with the expressiveness of a formalism for specifying properties of programs, which is relevant to programming languages. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is another likely category because the paper introduces a new type of automata and studies its closure and decidability properties. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible because the paper deals with the problem of language inclusion, which is a fundamental problem in algorithmic theory. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also less likely but possible because the paper deals with the specification and verification of real-time properties of software systems, which is relevant to software engineering.
